[9] Brazil (Sao Paulo state)
[The series of 6 reports from Indonesia are of interest because they
indicate the extent of dengue cases across that geographically
extensive country and because the outbreaks are larger than those
experienced last year [2006]. - Mod.TY]

******
[1] Indonesia (Jakarta)
Date: Fri 9 Dec 2007
Source: The Kola Post [in Indonesian, trans., edited]
<http://www.poskota.co.id/news_baca.asp?id=42183&ik=3>


The Special Capital District of Jakarta occupied the 1st level of
dengue fever [outbreak classification] for the length of 2007.

According to the Department of Health [2007] data entered up to 5 Dec
[2007], 134 847 cases that were reported [Nationally? In Java? - Mod.
TY], 30 469 cases were from Jakarta.

More than 30 percent of the cases of dengue fever came from Jakarta,
the Head of Health Service Special Capital District, Dr. Wibowo
Sukijat, MPH, said on Thursday (6 Dec [2007]). This number is an
increase compared to the previous year [2006] when there were 24 932
cases with 39 deaths.

This year [2007], of the 30 469 [dengue fever] sufferers who were
treated, 81 died.

There were several factors in Jakarta that account for why this area
had the highest numbers of dengue fever cases, including bad
environment, the mobility of many inhabitants, the inhabitants's
substantial population, as well as increased temperatures, so virus
[transmission] has been increasingly raging.

The [dengue virus mosquito vector] control campaign has not yet given
optimal results.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[An interactive map of Java, Indonesia, showing the location of
