[6] Indonesia (North Sulaweisi)
Date: 11 Dec 2007
Source: Harian Komentar [in Indonesian, trans. & summ., edited]
<http://www.hariankomentar.com/hl001.html>


Dengue fever and dengue hemorrhagic fever is raging in North
Sulawesi. Many patients (in general children) suffered dengue in
Manado City, Kabupaten Bolmong, Sangihe and in a part of Minahasa. At
this time more than one hospital was filled with dengue patients.

The Head Health Service North Sulawesi, Dr. Christian Ti-laar,
immediately dismissed warning related the dengue outbreak [which
appeared] together with the rainy season at this time.

Dealing with the problem of the spread of dengue fever is more than
his [agencies] responsibility, the regency/the city [must be
involved, too] because, this always has been routine every year.

Therefore he was not surprised that hospital wards were filled with
patients, said Tilaar to the reporter, on Tuesday (04 Dec [2007]).
"Of course," he continued, "the spread of dengue fever illnesses was
already anticipated a long time ago before the arrival of the rainy season."

Until now the only [dengue] prevention is by waging war on mosquitoes
that cause the spread. The method is the "3M" [that eliminates _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquito breeding sites]. Abate larvacide was also given.
These measures can control mosquitoes for several weeks but must be
repeated for longer control.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

